node.text: Have you ever tried to make anything from concrete? As for me?...Let’s just say that cement and I would not have been seat mates on the school bus. I have had lots of successes with cement but if you leave with one tip of the day from this diy...know that you should NEVER use “cement all” quick set when trying to shove cement into pantyhose and tie it up with rubber bands unless you work like a cheetah sprinting while on steroids. The Pinterest girls made it looks so easy. 🤔 I did actually have 3 that turned out...one even being out of the “cement all”. 😱I guess I might be part cheetah. #diyconcrete #concretepumpkin #diygonewrong

node.title: How NOT To Make Concrete Pumpkins

node.text: Mind over matter is all ya need for somersaults after three kids and floral arrangements. Chester was all in for it and rooting me on! I tried my best to show how I jam these florals into old pickling crocks. Did I inspire you to try a somersault? #doubledogdareya #floralarrangment #diyfloralarrangement

node.text: After six years of stripping, sanding, and crack picking, it’s finished! What do you think?! Are you surprised that I decided to use the old knobs? Did you think I would end up painting it? Since it won’t fit through any of our doors to get it inside, we are just going to hang out here in our new outdoor living room and sniff the mountain air while listening to the neighbor dogs. I couldn’t be happier with the way that it turned out and I’m so excited to use this in our new kitchen when we build for towels, utensils, and all the things! Oh and if you ever paint any cabinets blue, I will come for you. Oh, and I love you! 😘 #mapcabinet #printerscabinet #drawers #ididit

node.text: Pumpkin...I said the word...is it ok to say yet? 🤔 I’m showing my little “biting pods” tutorial and I even sang a little tune for you. Have you used these pods? I know we’ve had this conversation before but I can’t remember what the tree is called...can you drop the name in the comments here if you know it? I screen shot it last year when you told me but I can’t find it in the 19,459 photos in my camera roll. Just don’t get bit by the biting things that aren’t alive, if you use these... #disclaimer. Ok, anyways...here it is...and Chester helped...and there was no shaking, or baking. #falldecorhasbegun #falldiydecor

#sponsored Bry made us some sorbet today with our new ice cream maker from @walmart! node.text: (Swipe over) Can you believe your eyes? No sanding! 😱 I’m still amazed! I showed the whole process on the blog…link in profile. I shared how much I paid for this old antique hutch on the blog too. I’m super duper in love with it! its not that it wasn’t pretty before, but I love it even more now! Another piece DONE for the new house🙌🏼 #antiquehutch #bleached

node.text: Who like old things? 🙋🏼‍♀️ I might as well get some things done while I’m in here. Just because I’m trapped in this room, doesn’t mean I’m having a bad time. 😁 Picture hung, rearranging done, and most importantly, laundry thrown to the side. Oh and only 1+1 for nail holes….2 is better than 3. 😬 Thanks for all of your prayers and well wishes, my friends! 😘 #vintagefinds #antiquedecor

node.text: Swipe over for the shark attack😬Remember that one time when I didn’t parasail? Well, Hallie, Kaden, and Bry did and they loved it! I looked at them up there from the boat and patted myself on the back for not going. 😳 Kaden was the scardiest of all which was a little surprising. He said if it had been over land, he wouldn’t have been as scared…because ya know, that smashing to the ground on land would be much more comfortable than getting bit by a shark. 🦈 #parasailing #imsailing #noregrets

node.text: Do you think Richard is proud? Did you vote to keep the raw wood look or to white wash and glaze? I really had a tough time deciding because I loved the raw wood so much but Richard and I thought this old character look would look good. I love it! I hope it looks good with the leather! 😍 I used the same white wash and glaze technique that I used on my hutch (on the blog) #deconstructedchair

node.text: Do you love searching for shells too? I won’t tell. 🤫 Shell hunting is always a highlight of our trips to the beach! I had a lot of you asking what I was planning on doing with them…nothing spectacular really, just adding some memories to a jar. ♥️🐚 #shells #shellhunting #shelldecor

node.text:
(Swipe over) When we moved into this rental, I wasn’t too fond of the back patio/yard area, but now, since I finished fixing it up, I love it! #ad(more on the blog, in profile)
.
.
We also just added the Caséta by Lutron Outdoor Smart Plug to our back patio and it’s amazing!!! We can now turn our lights on and off from the @lutronelectronics app on our phone, no matter where we are! I used to forget to turn our string lights off before we would go to bed and I wouldn’t realize it until I was already asleep and then woken up again from the light beaming in! Now we can program them to come on and turn off whenever we would like with the Outdoor Smart Plug, or turn them off from our phone, while sitting in bed! We love Caséta by Lutron!!! 
.
.
#CasetaSmarterLighting #CasetaChallenge #casetawireless #backpatio #patio
